meanings":["English (Midlands): variant of   Bennett  ."]},{"name":"Bennetts","meanings":["English (Cornwall): variant of   Bennett  , with genitival or post-medieval excrescent <i>-s</i>."]},{"name":"Dittus","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Gerhard, Fritz, Kurt, Otto, Reinhold.","German: from a vernacular short form of the Latin personal name <i>Benedictus</i> (see   Bennett  )."]},{"name":"Benedict","meanings":["English, German, and Dutch: from the personal name <i>Benedict</i>, from Latin <i>Benedictus</i> ‘blessed’. This owed its popularity in the Middle Ages chiefly to Saint Benedict of Norcia (<i>c.</i> 480–550), who founded the Benedictine order of monks at Monte Cassino and wrote a monastic rule that formed a model for all subsequent rules. No doubt the meaning of the Latin word also contributed to its popularity as a personal name, especially in Romance countries. Occasionally the English surname may derive from Latin <i>benedicite</i> ‘bless (you)’, perhaps given as a nickname to an habitual user of the expression. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed the German variant <b>Benedikt</b> and many cognates from other languages, e.g. Hungarian   Benedek  , Slovenian <b>Benedik</b> (see   Benedick  ), and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Italian   Benedetti  ."]},{"name":"Bennette","meanings":["English (Cornwall): altered form of   Bennett  ."]},{"name":"Benett","meanings":["English: variant of   Bennett  ."]},{"name":"Bennight","meanings":["Probably an altered form of English   Bennett  ."]},{"name":"Bennison","meanings":["English: patronymic from the Middle English personal name <i>Bene(i)t</i> + <i>-son</i>. See   Bennett   and compare   Benson  ."]}]},{"name":"Goodwife","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Americanized form of German <b>Gut(t)wein</b>, literally ‘good wine’, but probably derived from the personal name <i>Guotwin</i> from Old High German <i>guot</i> ‘good’ + <i>win(e)</i> ‘friend’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Goodwife Bennett was born in 1485, in Chetnole, Dorset, England, her father, Thomas Bennett, was 26 and her mother, Elizabeth Selby, was 26. She married William Winterhay in 1506, in Dorset, England. They were the parents of at least 3 sons and 4 daughters. She died about 1545, in England, United Kingdom, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1485–about 1545":"1485–umbes 1545","1485–1545":"1485–1545","1481–1506":"1481–1506","1507–1577":"1507–1577","1571–Female":"1571–Surnud","1573–Male":"1573–Surnud","1577–Male":"1577–Surnud","1579–Female":"1579–Surnud","1581–Female":"1581–Surnud","1583–Female":"1583–Surnud","1459–1509":"1459–1509","1459–1535":"1459–1535","1583":"1583","1472":"1472","1571":"1571","1581":"1581","1481":"1481","1459":"1459","1535":"1535","1579":"1579","1545":"1545","1577":"1577","about 1545":"umbes 1545","1485":"1485","1573":"1573","1509":"1509","1507":"1507","1506":"1506","Chetnoll, Dorset, England":"Chetnole, Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Newbury, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom":"Newbury, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Berkshire, England":"Berkshire, England","England":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Dorset, England, United Kingdom":"Dorset, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Chetnole, Dorset, England":"Chetnole, Dorset, England"},"fi":{"1485–about 1545":"1485–noin 1545","1485–1545":"1485–1545","1481–1506":"1481–1506","1507–1577":"1507–1577","1571–Female":"1571–Kuollut","1573–Male":"1573–Kuollut","1577–Male":"1577–Kuollut","1579–Female":"1579–Kuollut","1581–Female":"1581–Kuollut","1583–Female":"1583–Kuollut","1459–1509":"1459–1509","1459–1535":"1459–1535","1583":"1583","1472":"1472","1571":"1571","1581":"1581","1481":"1481","1459":"1459","1535":"1535","1579":"1579","1545":"1545","1577":"1577","about 1545":"noin 1545","1485":"1485","1573":"1573","1509":"1509","1507":"1507","1506":"1506","Chetnoll, Dorset, England":"Chetnole, Dorset, Englanti, Yh